=== Etymology ===
From Old French '''[[rivière]]''' < Vulgar Latin '''*riparia''' (riverbank, seashore, river) < Latin '''[[riparius]]''' (of a riverbank) < '''[[riparia]]''' (shore) < '''[[ripa]]''' (river bank) < Proto-Indo-European base '''*[[rei-]]''' (to scratch, tear, cut).

=== Noun ===
'''river''' ([[rivers]])

#A large [[stream]] of water that alters the nearby landscape. Occasionally rivers overflow their [[bank]]s and cause [[flood]]s.
#Any large flow of a [[liquid]] in a single body (e.g., 'a river of blood').

